      "content": "the problem is the \"temporary\" part. that's the part i can't get past. even when i sleep, the weight is still there when i wake up. it's like this constant, crushing pressure that never actually goes away. i feel like i'm just managing the pain instead of actually finding relief. what if the only way to actually get that stillness you're talking about is something more than just a nap or a break? like, a way to actually be done with the noise for good?",
